data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each one with the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer accepts expression trees

The setter parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your manual expression-tree code **won't compile**.

**Fix** — replace with a simple lambda:
```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type columns — names are now auto-uniquified

Two breaking changes here:

- **Same-level duplicates** (`ShippingAddress.Street` / `BillingAddress.Street`) now get a numeric suffix instead of silently sharing a column.
- **Nested complex types** use the **full path** (`Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of `BillingAddress_City`).

This will generate a migration that renames columns, breaking your existing schema.

**Fix** — pin the old column names explicitly:
```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// For nested types, pin the old short name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging).

**Fix** — add the parameter to your implementation:
```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
{
    // Use logCommandText for logging (may have constants redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
}
```

Update all other methods on the interface similarly (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
